cosmic-nightlight (0.3.1-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Fix "Start on login" being ignored: the package auto-enabled the systemd
    user service, which started the daemon on every login regardless of the
    in-app toggle. The service is no longer auto-enabled (the toggle's XDG
    autostart entry is now the single source of truth), and the postinst undoes
    any prior enablement and removes the orphaned pre-rename "nightshift" unit.
  * autostart toggle now also clears legacy ("nightshift") autostart entries and
    reflects them in its state, so upgrades from the old name behave correctly.
  * uninstall.sh now stops/disables the daemon, removes the autostart entry, and
    resets the screen tint, so uninstalling no longer leaves the screen warm or a
    daemon re-tinting on the next login.

 -- Daniel Watts <danielcwtts@gmail.com>  Mon, 15 Jun 2026 16:00:00 +0000

cosmic-nightlight (0.3.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Rename the project from "Night Shift" to "Night Light" to avoid trademark
    confusion. Crates, binaries, the app ID (now io.github.cosmic_nightlight),
    desktop entries, the polkit rule, and the systemd unit are all renamed.
    NOTE: the config directory moves to
    ~/.config/cosmic/io.github.cosmic_nightlight/, so prior settings are not
    carried over automatically.
  * Add a manual on/off override that takes precedence over the schedule and
    automatically clears at the next sunset/sunrise transition.
  * Sync settings live between the applet, settings window, and daemon via a
    cosmic_config file watcher.
  * Harden the daemon: wait for the graphical session to be foreground before
    touching DRM at login, and retry failed applies with backoff instead of
    assuming success.
  * Settings window: mirror the applet's on/off toggle and temperature, show a
    schedule status line, honour the system 12/24-hour clock, and enforce a
    minimum window size.
  * Add scripts/uninstall.sh to remove installed components.

 -- Daniel Watts <danielcwtts@gmail.com>  Mon, 15 Jun 2026 12:30:00 +0000

cosmic-nightlight (0.2.0-1) noble; urgency=medium

  * Move the GUI into a COSMIC panel applet.
    - Status-bar icon with a popup for the on/off toggle and temperature
      slider.
    - New `--settings` window for autostart, schedule mode, sunset/sunrise
      hours, and night temperature.
    - Settings are now shared via cosmic_config across the applet, settings
      window, and daemon.
    - Autostart toggle writes an XDG autostart entry that runs the daemon
      and re-applies the saved tint on login.
    - Settings window content now scrolls when the window is shrunk.

 -- Daniel Watts <danielcwtts@gmail.com>  Sun, 14 Jun 2026 23:11:12 -0500

